programme.title: Nightscape: Dark Reign of Thanatos
programme.desc: In Nightscape: Dark Reign of Thanatos, the ultimate struggle between man and the Gods takes place. Upon creating the earth the great god Zelos grew weary and so forged in his image two sons to uphold his kingdom and ensure its longevity, Aevum and Thanatos. As time progressed, so did the intentions of the two sons. The second, Thanatos poisoned himself against the will of his brother and turned to blackness and evil for answers. From this new hatred, the darkness bore a final battle to end the rule of either son- for their father lay dormant, undisturbed and unaware of his failing hopes.Years later, Thanatos threatens the very existence of our world, but something is still preventing him from total domination as the future of all humanity lies in the balance.

programme.title: Paranormal Haunting: The Curse of the Blue Moon Inn
programme.desc: High on the peak of the Moors stands the Blue Moon Inn, the home of Matthew Hopkins for as long as anybody cares to remember. Here is the place where once every century the moon appears to turn blue and all-manner of strange and terrifying events are unleashed upon the land. The time has come again and with it a small group of interested individuals. An astronomer, an astrologer and a documentary filmmaker all arrive unaware of the pure evil that will befall them. A nightmare unfolds upon each guest until the final shocking conclusion. Prepare for witchcraft, occult rituals and answers to age-old mysteries. Prepare yourselves for the Blue Moon Inn.

programme.title: Muckman
programme.desc: Mickey O'Hara is a television producer on the skids whose career was virtually destroyed when his attempt to discover the legendary backwoods demon Muckman was exposed as a pathetic fraud on live television. Using his in with sexy trash TV personality Asia Buchanan (Anju McIntyre) as leverage he persuades small time cable mogul Otto Van Sant to give him one last chance to redeem himself. Claiming a secret source in the backwoods of Pennsylvania, Mickey and Asia, along with technical crew Jerome “Curly” Baker, Drew Simmons, production manager Pauline Stark and able assistant Billie Mulligan set off to find and exploit the Muckie Mystery. They’re met in the middle of nowhere by Cletus Hobbs, Mickey’s secret source, who leads them to the cabin which will be their home base for the production. After a disastrous first night Cletus meets them in the morning accompanied by his cretinous cousins Horace and Elmer, who take the gang to their “Muckman Mooseum” on the edge of a nearby swamp. Various Muckman artifacts, including a Muckman skull under glass, are on display. More convincing is the unearthly howl the crew hears outside the museum. Giving chase, the gang sees a hirsute figure fleeing through the woods (leaving behind the unbearable stench characteristic of Muckman), capturing a glimpse of the creature on tape. That night they get an even better look at the monster when it attacks their cabin, and the following evening when the crew attempts to document the capture of the creature in a trap set by Cletus and his boys all hell breaks loose. The creature appears big as life. Chaos ensues, there is blood and dismemberment, but all is not as it seems. Cletus and his gang have their own agenda, as do Mickey and Asia, and even Billie knows more than she lets on. In the end there are more things loose in the woods than anyone suspects, and the swamps unleash a few secrets as well.

programme.title: Owen's Top Tips For Hunting Late Season, 2 Iowa Bucks In 2 Days
programme.desc: On this week's episode, we kick things off with Josh Sparks who gives us an update on what's to come in the next few episodes along with an announcement that our Chasing November apparel is now back in stock. Follow the link below if you are interested! Next, we catch up with Owen Reigler who takes us through a few of his favorite late season tips and strategies. Owen discusses setup options and some things to keep in mind when trying to fill a buck tag this time of the year. After that, we follow him to the blind for the opening day of Iowa's late muzzleloader season where he hopes to tag one of multiple mature bucks that he encountered while scouting only a few days prior. Lastly, we rejoin Justin Karns and his partner in crime Drake Lamb as the duo hit the woods again, this time looking to fill Justin's late muzzleloader tag. The plan works perfect and the team's success continues. We hope you enjoy, and as always, thank you immensely for your support every week!

programme.title: Creative Tractor Access Leads To Big Buck, How To Use A Decoy In The Late Season
programme.desc: On this episode of Midwest Whitetail, we kick things off in northern Missouri with Tyler Behlmann and his brother-in-law Jimmy Manaska. The duo are heading to the field in hopes of repeating the success achieved during the previous two hunting seasons. After an introduction to bowhunting back in 2021, Jimmy has successfully harvested two bucks over the span of two hunts and looks to capitalize on another using a decoy in early December. With less than ideal conditions, Tyler gets creative with his access using a tractor and deploys a decoy that proves to be the difference maker. Then a few weeks later, we head to southern Iowa with Kaleb Greiner who is back after it with the bow in hand. Following multiple success stories with family and friends during the late season, he hopes to close out the 2023 season on a high note. After taking note of rutting activity deep into the late season the previous year, Kaleb decides to bring a buck decoy mounted to his bow and the hunt that follows is hard to make up! Be sure to tune in tomorrow as we bring another action packed episode of hunting to you and as always, thank you so much for all of the support.

programme.title: When To Introduce Your Kids To Hunting With Mike, Best Late Season Ever
programme.desc: On this episode of Midwest Whitetail, we sit down with Mike Reed as he reflects on the past six years introducing his five kids to deer hunting. Mike goes over how he has chose to develop a love and passion for the outdoors through hunting and highlights some things that have been successful for him in doing so! The goal for Late Muzzleloader season in Iowa for Mike was to get all of his kids who wanted to hunt a buck. With a few days left in the season, that goal was achieved. We kick things off with Bella Reed on the Home Farm as she is hoping to catch up with Anna's buck but is met with a BIG surprise! The next evening Mike took Xander to a new farm in hopes of tagging his first deer and with light fading an Iowa stud stepped out of the corn. Finally Xanders twin brother Tate was up to bat and unlike Bella and Xander, Tate went on a five day excursion after his first Iowa buck, and what a buck its was. A River Farm legend. The stellar year for Mike and his family could easily be there best one ever. As always, we appreciate you taking the time to tune into this week's episode and thank you so much for your support!

programme.title: Buck Tag Filled In A Blizzard, Three Perfect Deer Hunts
programme.desc: On this week's episode of Midwest Whitetail we kick things off with Josh Sparks who tees up what to expect timeline wise for our final episodes as we round out the season. Following that we jump over to Kaleb Greiner who offers up a tip that he's been deploying the past few late season's to help wildlife in harsh conditions. Then we jump to three perfect deer hunts to continue the trend of big bucks and memories made in Iowa. Up first is Casey Murrey who tags a brute of a buck with Kaleb behind the camera for the special hunt. Next Devin Wills continues the dream season by tagging a buck in a blizzard. Finally, on the last day of the Iowa deer season, Rye Ludwig lays the hammer on his first buck of the year. We hope you enjoy the episode and as always, thank you so much for the continued support!

programme.title: Giant Late Season Buck With A Bow, Zach's Journey As A First Time Landowner
programme.desc: On this week's episode of Midwest Whitetail, we ride alongside with Zach Rozmus for an incredible multi-year journey. One that saw Zach and his wife buy their first farm and the moments that lead to Zach punching his first ever landowner tag on a great buck. "Area 52" underwent a variety of land improvements including preparing the available tillable ground for future uses, TSI and logging operations to enhance the available cover for wildlife, and numerous food plots to hunt the property effectively. In short, this is Zach's How-To manual for a first time land owner based on his experience. After many close calls and thrilling encounters with mature bucks over the years, the hard work finally culminates into an action packed late season hunt for a buck Zach calls "T-Bone." We hope you enjoy the story of Zach's first ever buck harvest on his own dirt and learn a few things along the way! As we say each and every week, we cannot be more grateful for the support this year and look forward to closing out the 2023 season on a high note with two more episodes to come!

programme.title: Surviving Mann
programme.desc: The stakes continue to climb as Green Light Sights rewards one top shooter with their very own custom weapon—proof that precision pays off. But there's no time to celebrate. Bear Arms ups the ante by issuing defense vests to every contestant, with one hard rule: once it’s on, it stays on. From grueling mission briefings to body armor plank challenges that push endurance to the brink, the weight—literally and mentally—never lets up. Still armored, the team reports to Ken Shamrock for another brutal dose of Lion’s Den physical punishment. Just when they think they’ve caught a break, Compliant Technologies’ infamous glove makes a shocking return to torment a fresh round of contestants. And as the day winds down, Don introduces the team to his personal “Flights” challenge—an unforgiving test no one is excited to take on. It all ends with a sobering CIA reminder: in the field, your backstory might just save your life—or end it.

programme.title: Surviving Mann
programme.desc: This week, memory meets mission as contestants face off in a high-stakes Kim’s Game challenge—designed to sharpen recall under pressure with 100 points and team leadership on the line. With observation, speed, and accuracy all in play, remembering every detail could make or break the mission. As the team pushes forward, it’s time to dig deeper. Contestants open up about their backstories, revealing the powerful personal reasons that brought them to the toughest reality show on earth. Some are here to prove something. Others? To fight for more than just themselves. The action intensifies as Hoffner Knives returns with a brutal tactical evolution, testing shooting and blade skills with precision under pressure. A split-second difference determines the winner of a major reward—proving that in this game, every tenth of a second matters. The day wraps with a visit from HCA Precision Barrels and one final classroom lesson—a pointed reminder that in the world of elite operators, your story is your strength… or your downfall.

programme.title: Wild Shots
programme.desc: In this episode of Wild Shots, Tim Harmsen heads to the heart of American gun craftsmanship with an exclusive, behind-the-scenes tour of Palmetto State Armory, where freedom is literally built on the production floor. From the anodizing line to live assembly, Tim witnesses American ingenuity in action as a rifle comes to life before his eyes. With the epic 10,000-Round Challenge complete, it’s time for some serious maintenance. The crew at SEAL 1 steps in with their cutting-edge nanotechnology to give the battle-worn BCM AK the deep clean it deserves. Once the guns are gleaming, it’s time to send rounds downrange. Teaming up with top firearms influencer Sootch, Tim takes aim at a new challenge, including a 1,000-yard Wild Shot that pushes precision, patience, and performance to the limit.

programme.title: Fortress
programme.desc: In the premiere of Fortress, Sheriff Mark Lamb and co-hosts explore America’s urgent need for security—both personal and societal. They meet a passionate team turning donated land into a homestead that feeds and shelters trafficking survivors. Then, CCW Safe steps in to showcase how legal protection for concealed carriers can be the line between justice and ruin. Powerful stories of resilience, protection, and purpose unfold in this compelling first episode.
